Schema Definition for Meta

 The set of Identifiers for the VBO or component. These should be used to uniquely identifier instances of the business object or component. The identifier of the business object or component. This should be used to identify instances of a business object or component. Where the component is being used to reference another business object then this is the primary key of the target object. Use the attributes @schemeName and @schemeAgencyName to identify type of Identifier. The name of the instance of a business object or component. A free text description of a business object or component. The @actionCode attribute is used within a modification operation to indicate the action (add, update, delete) intended on a component. Base type for all business objects and some components. A classification of the business object or component. This identifies the sub-type of the instance of object or component. The set of classifications for the business object or component. A classification applied to the business object or component. More than one classification scheme can be applied using the @listName attribute to identify the type of code list being used. The classification scheme can be used to group instances of the object or component. An indication of the hierarchy level of the category when involved in a hierarchical classification, e.g. level 1 -> Category/@listHierarchyID=1, level 2 -> Category/@listHierarchyID=2. In this case the listName should be the same for each level to show their relationship. The lifecycle state of the business object or component. This field is used to track the specific state an instance of an object or component is in, e.g. the Customer Bill is Active or the Customer Request has been Cancelled.
